#rolling means
w = 5
aapl_rolling_mean = aapl['Adj Close'].rolling(w).mean().dropna()
ibm_rolling_mean = ibm['Adj Close'].rolling(w).mean().dropna()
jpm_rolling_mean = jpm['Adj Close'].rolling(w).mean().dropna()
djx_rolling_mean = djx['Adj Close'].rolling(w).mean().dropna()
#rolling median
aapl_rolling_med = aapl['Adj Close'].rolling(w).median().dropna()
ibm_rolling_med = ibm['Adj Close'].rolling(w).median().dropna()
jpm_rolling_med = jpm['Adj Close'].rolling(w).median().dropna()
djx_rolling_med = djx['Adj Close'].rolling(w).median().dropna()
#mean absolute deviation
aapl_mad = (abs(aapl_rolling_med - aapl_rolling_med.rolling(5).median())).median()
ibm_mad = (abs(ibm_rolling_med - ibm_rolling_med.rolling(5).median())).median()
jpm_mad = (abs(jpm_rolling_med - jpm_rolling_med.rolling(5).median())).median()
djx_mad = (abs(djx_rolling_med - djx_rolling_med.rolling(5).median())).median()
aapl_mad

outliers = ['2018-05-14','2018-09-14','2018-12-14','2019-01-14']
aapl_max = aapl['Adj Close'].max()*1.2
ibm_max = ibm['Adj Close'].max()*1.2
jpm_max = jpm['Adj Close'].max()*1.2
djx_max = djx['Adj Close'].max()*1.2

for i in outliers:
    aapl.loc[datetime.strptime(i,'%Y-%m-%d'),'Adj Close'] = aapl_max
    ibm.loc[datetime.strptime(i,'%Y-%m-%d'),'Adj Close'] = ibm_max
    jpm.loc[datetime.strptime(i,'%Y-%m-%d'),'Adj Close'] = jpm_max
    djx.loc[datetime.strptime(i,'%Y-%m-%d'),'Adj Close'] = djx_max
